        <briefdescription>
<para>Functions in <ref refid="xadcps__intr_8c" kindref="compound">xadcps_intr.c</ref>. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>This function enables the specified interrupts in the device.</para><para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>InstancePtr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>is a pointer to the <ref refid="struct_x_adc_ps" kindref="compound">XAdcPs</ref> instance. </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>Mask</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>is the bit-mask of the interrupts to be enabled. Bit positions of 1 will be enabled. Bit positions of 0 will keep the previous setting. This mask is formed by OR&apos;ing XADCPS_INTX_* bits defined in <ref refid="xadcps__hw_8h" kindref="compound">xadcps_hw.h</ref>.</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>None.</para></simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>None. </para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
